WEBVTT

00:06.006 --> 00:08.258
[dramatic music playing]

00:12.095 --> 00:13.680
[lightning crackling]

00:14.931 --> 00:16.975
[shining]

00:17.058 --> 00:19.436
What just happened?

00:23.273 --> 00:26.067
I'll never let you go.

00:26.151 --> 00:30.196
[heroic music playing]

00:39.706 --> 00:41.624
The shard.

00:41.708 --> 00:43.209
You all right, Capt'n?

00:43.293 --> 00:44.961
Aye, Batten.

00:45.045 --> 00:46.713
What happened to Sonic, Captain?

00:46.796 --> 00:50.925
He poofed!
And in the blue flash, he was gone.

00:51.009 --> 00:52.761
The Devil's Lighthouse!

00:52.844 --> 00:56.848
Aye! And with this,
we will reclaim the No Place Seas.

00:56.931 --> 00:59.184
-Huzzah!
-Huzzah!

00:59.267 --> 01:02.228
This craft is the property
of The Chaos Council.

01:02.312 --> 01:04.147
Shut your metal gob!

01:04.230 --> 01:07.692
I will not! I was programmed
by The Chaos Council

01:07.776 --> 01:10.111
with the mission to retrieve that shard.

01:10.195 --> 01:11.362
And ya failed!

01:11.446 --> 01:16.367
The council will return.
You would do best to surrender to me now.

01:16.451 --> 01:18.244
[crew laughs]

01:18.328 --> 01:22.082
If this Chaos Council
wants to take this ship back,

01:22.165 --> 01:25.335
they're more than welcome to try.

01:25.418 --> 01:30.632
You're a heck of a scrapper, Rusty.
Ye'll make a fine pirate.

01:30.715 --> 01:33.343
I am loyal to the Chaos Council.

01:33.426 --> 01:35.220
Then prisoner it is.

01:35.303 --> 01:40.433
All right, crew, let's get this metal boat
ship-shape and ready to sail!

01:40.517 --> 01:42.352
[crew cheers]

01:42.894 --> 01:45.522
What about the Angel's Voyage, Captain?

01:45.605 --> 01:48.983
A good captain goes down with their ship,

01:49.067 --> 01:51.778
but a great captain steals someone else's.

01:51.861 --> 01:53.822
Ha! What be her name?

01:53.905 --> 01:55.323
The Kraken.

01:55.406 --> 01:58.326
Aye, a fitting name.

01:58.409 --> 01:59.410
♪ Oh! ♪

01:59.494 --> 02:03.414
♪ Who'd be the scourge
of The Great No Place Sea? ♪

02:03.498 --> 02:04.958
[crew] ♪ Dread! It be Dread! ♪

02:05.041 --> 02:06.376
[theme music playing]

02:16.386 --> 02:18.972
[seagulls squawking]

02:21.933 --> 02:25.520
[yelling]

02:28.815 --> 02:31.109
[yelling] Not again!

02:33.570 --> 02:36.114
[gasps, coughs]

02:36.197 --> 02:38.658
Oh, I really thought I had it this time.

02:39.242 --> 02:43.454
Okay, how do I find a band of pirates
in the middle of a massive ocean world?

02:44.289 --> 02:47.125
Hmm. I need to get some higher ground.

02:49.335 --> 02:50.795
The Devil's Lighthouse!

02:52.088 --> 02:53.298
[whoosh]

02:58.761 --> 03:01.431
The Yolkomotive is primed and loaded.

03:01.514 --> 03:06.561
Egg-cellent! We are on a tight schedule
here, doctors, so no messing around.

03:06.644 --> 03:10.231
Don't tell me what to do!
We'll get the power shard.

03:10.315 --> 03:12.442
Don't you worry about it.

03:12.525 --> 03:15.111
[Dr. Deep] And in record time, I'd wager.

03:15.194 --> 03:17.614
[whoosh]

03:17.697 --> 03:22.493
If we want to find the shard,
we need to find Rusty Rose.

03:23.453 --> 03:24.996
[Knuckles The Dread] Black Rose!

03:25.079 --> 03:28.541
Set a course for me long awaiting destiny.

03:28.625 --> 03:30.376
Aye, aye, Capt'n!

03:30.460 --> 03:32.712
All finished with the banners, Dread.

03:32.795 --> 03:34.881
[Knuckles The Dread] Fine job, lad!

03:34.964 --> 03:37.216
And the cannon's been locked and loaded!

03:37.300 --> 03:40.345
Good! Let's go get our pirate on.

03:41.346 --> 03:42.513
Huh?

03:43.223 --> 03:44.641
[Dr. Deep] Filthy Pirates!

03:44.724 --> 03:47.352
Surrender the shard and we will leave you

03:47.435 --> 03:50.647
with your stolen ship
and your pathetic lives.

03:50.730 --> 03:55.985
The Chaos Council has come for me
and the shard just as I said they would.

03:56.069 --> 03:57.487
They can have you back!

03:57.570 --> 03:59.030
If he wants me beauty,

03:59.113 --> 04:02.242
he can come down here and take it from me!

04:02.325 --> 04:03.785
Bring it!

04:03.868 --> 04:06.829
[mechanical whirring]

04:12.543 --> 04:15.588
[battle cries]

04:17.799 --> 04:20.051
[battle cry]

04:20.134 --> 04:22.804
You can't have it! It's mine! Mine!

04:22.887 --> 04:25.056
-[electricity crackling]
-[grunts]

04:27.100 --> 04:28.226
[grunts]

04:31.771 --> 04:36.317
No! When I get me hands
on ye lousy landlubbing lunatics,

04:36.401 --> 04:38.486
-I'll take me sword and--
-[beep, mutes]

04:38.569 --> 04:41.072
That filthy sea dog put up a fight.

04:41.155 --> 04:44.742
Eggforcers! Give them a final volley
to remember us by.

04:44.826 --> 04:47.829
[robots chattering]

04:50.373 --> 04:53.001
[Eggforcer] All systems
are fully disabled, Captain.

04:53.084 --> 04:55.253
[both] Eggcellent.

04:55.336 --> 04:58.589
-[Dr. Done It] What about Rusty Rose?
-Leave her.

04:58.673 --> 05:01.426
She's failed us one too many times.

05:04.929 --> 05:06.681
They are... [short circuit]

05:06.764 --> 05:08.016
...leaving me.

05:14.897 --> 05:16.816
[ringing]

05:16.899 --> 05:19.944
[beep]

05:21.321 --> 05:23.906
[incomprehensible static]

05:23.990 --> 05:25.533
Fellow doctors.

05:25.616 --> 05:28.244
We have The No Place Shard
in our possession.

05:28.328 --> 05:30.246
Securing in record time, I might add.

05:30.997 --> 05:33.958
Ugh! Those two mouth breathers
are always rubbing it in.

05:34.500 --> 05:36.753
We're picking up a converter from New Yoke

05:36.836 --> 05:40.923
and then we're on route.
Send us your coordinates and be ready.

05:41.007 --> 05:42.216
Affirmative!

05:42.300 --> 05:45.887
-Our egg-xact coordinates are--
-[static fuzz]

05:45.970 --> 05:49.140
Transmission faulty. Repeat coordinates.

05:49.223 --> 05:51.517
Looks like they have a problem
with their tech.

05:51.601 --> 05:53.436
What a shocker.

05:53.519 --> 05:55.730
This is too easy.

05:56.606 --> 05:58.900
-[whoosh]
-[dramatic music playing]

06:11.162 --> 06:13.664
Smoke! And another Egg ship.

06:13.748 --> 06:15.875
That's gotta be Dread.

06:15.958 --> 06:19.003
-Sonic! The Chaos Council have the shard!
-Nine?

06:19.087 --> 06:20.963
I bought you some time. You gotta hurry

06:21.047 --> 06:23.633
if you're gonna get it back
before The Mothership.

06:23.716 --> 06:26.969
Thanks, pal. And don't worry,
hurrying is what I do best.

06:27.053 --> 06:28.930
-[beep]
-[whoosh]

06:31.682 --> 06:33.559
Wonder what happened to those pirates?

06:33.643 --> 06:37.271
Okay, if I'm gonna catch that ship,
I'm gonna need to get airborne.

06:37.355 --> 06:40.525
[Sonic grunts]

06:40.608 --> 06:41.859
We can't, Captain!

06:41.943 --> 06:43.486
-[crew gasps]
-Yo-ho, pirates!

06:43.569 --> 06:45.530
-[Knuckles grunts]
-[grunts]

06:45.613 --> 06:47.490
[crew] Sonic?

06:47.573 --> 06:49.033
You're back?

06:49.117 --> 06:50.201
That's right!

06:50.284 --> 06:53.121
Those scurvy eggheads stole me beauty.

06:53.204 --> 06:57.083
I heard. Your... beauty, huh?
Hmm, well, whatever you're calling it,

06:57.166 --> 06:59.085
we have to get it back
and I need your help.

07:00.586 --> 07:03.381
Come on! We have to get this ship moving
and go after them.

07:03.464 --> 07:06.092
The ship is damaged
and we're not going anywhere.

07:06.175 --> 07:08.970
[Rusty] I can fix The Kraken.

07:09.053 --> 07:13.099
Yeah, Rusty can fix it!
Wait, is she your prisoner?

07:13.182 --> 07:14.475
What about The Council?

07:14.559 --> 07:18.396
Aye, she's loyal to her beloved Council.

07:18.479 --> 07:21.023
That was before they desserted me.

07:21.107 --> 07:24.986
[short circuits] I will join your crew.

07:25.069 --> 07:29.574
We will make them regret
tossing me aside like scrap metal.

07:30.199 --> 07:31.826
Seems legit!

07:31.909 --> 07:34.620
Do ye agree to follow me orders?

07:34.704 --> 07:35.580
Aye.

07:35.663 --> 07:40.501
And do you swear to wreak vengeance
on those who stole me beauty?

07:40.585 --> 07:42.712
I... just said that.

07:43.463 --> 07:45.339
Rose, cut her loose!

07:46.966 --> 07:50.678
Yes! This team's really starting
to come together!

07:52.221 --> 07:56.392
Hmm, his speed will be useful
in getting me beauty back.

07:56.476 --> 07:57.685
[laughs maliciously]

07:58.186 --> 08:00.688
Good to be back
on the same side again, huh?

08:00.771 --> 08:02.940
It is a means to an end.

08:03.024 --> 08:06.652
Ouch. That hurts. She'll come around.

08:06.736 --> 08:08.738
You think you can fix it?

08:09.530 --> 08:10.615
Definitely.

08:11.032 --> 08:13.951
I don't know. I couldn't get it working.

08:14.452 --> 08:18.956
Rerouting stored energy
from solar collectors to ignition systems.

08:19.040 --> 08:21.250
Overwriting safety protocols.

08:21.334 --> 08:24.629
Rebooting main drive
and engine sub-systems.

08:25.254 --> 08:27.632
[booting up noises]

08:33.304 --> 08:35.097
[crew] Huzzah!

08:35.932 --> 08:38.184
Pfft! Lucky guess.

08:38.267 --> 08:41.521
You two are actually a lot alike,
you know that?

08:41.604 --> 08:43.523
[both in unison] We are nothing alike!

08:43.606 --> 08:45.274
Yeah, nothing same-y about that.

08:47.902 --> 08:49.487
[engines roaring]

08:49.570 --> 08:50.947
[groaning]

08:51.030 --> 08:52.990
-Did you try--
-Of course I tried that!

08:53.074 --> 08:55.201
-How about overriding the--
-Don't you think

08:55.284 --> 08:56.827
that was the first thing I did?

08:56.911 --> 09:01.457
This is frustrating!
I can't find a single thing wrong with it.

09:01.541 --> 09:03.292
-[explosion]
-[alarm blaring]

09:03.376 --> 09:05.419
We've been hit! What's going on?

09:09.799 --> 09:14.136
The Kraken? It can't be!
We left it dead in the water!

09:14.220 --> 09:17.098
Apparently, not dead enough!

09:19.392 --> 09:21.394
Rusty Rose.

09:21.477 --> 09:23.896
I told you we should've taken her with us!

09:23.980 --> 09:25.773
-No, you did not!
-[groans]

09:25.856 --> 09:27.400
Well, I thought it!

09:27.483 --> 09:29.735
We made a mistake
in not sinking them earlier,

09:29.819 --> 09:34.407
one we'll rectify at once.
Eggforcers, destroy The Kraken!

09:34.490 --> 09:36.158
[Eggforces chatter]

09:36.242 --> 09:38.452
[dramatic music playing]

09:42.373 --> 09:45.626
We can't get any altitude
with this damaged engine!

09:45.710 --> 09:50.047
Then turn off the autopilot
and let me show these rodents what's what.

09:50.131 --> 09:52.174
Oh... Okay, Gramps!

09:52.258 --> 09:56.053
Buckle up.
I'll show you how a real pilot can fly.

09:56.137 --> 09:59.557
Well, I'm launching another squad
of Eggforcers, then.

09:59.640 --> 10:01.183
[Dr. Deep] Fine! See if I care.

10:01.267 --> 10:04.103
[Eggforcers whirring]

10:04.186 --> 10:08.608
Hang on to your boots!
Time to get what we came for.

10:11.068 --> 10:12.778
Got 'em!

10:12.862 --> 10:14.030
[explosion]

10:14.113 --> 10:16.449
I have eliminated two.

10:18.826 --> 10:20.119
I knocked four!

10:22.121 --> 10:23.581
Make that ten!

10:23.664 --> 10:25.416
-[explosion]
-Twelve!

10:25.499 --> 10:27.460
-[Rusty] Thirteen!
-[Black] Fourteen!

10:27.543 --> 10:28.919
[both] Fifteen!

10:30.046 --> 10:31.380
[explosion]

10:31.464 --> 10:33.257
[thudding]

10:33.341 --> 10:36.427
We're getting killed out here.
Where's the Mothership?

10:36.510 --> 10:40.306
Enough! Lemme show you
how it's done, sonny.

10:40.389 --> 10:43.768
Here is the thing, old man,
I'm the driver.

10:43.851 --> 10:47.313
You go down to the engine room
and fix the communication motherboard.

10:47.396 --> 10:49.148
[both grunting]

10:49.231 --> 10:52.985
You can't drive worth a darn!
You go down to the engine room

10:53.069 --> 10:54.987
and fix the communication motherboard.

10:55.071 --> 10:57.365
Ugh! Fine! I'll do it.

10:57.448 --> 10:59.617
Just get us in position for pick up.

10:59.700 --> 11:04.580
[grunts] All right, now, first,
we gotta shake these slouchers loose.

11:04.664 --> 11:05.873
[dramatic music playing]

11:08.084 --> 11:11.587
Hang on te yer p'tatoes, we be goin' in!

11:11.671 --> 11:13.547
Are we going under the water?

11:13.631 --> 11:15.132
But we're still outside!

11:15.216 --> 11:17.802
[time slows]

11:26.352 --> 11:29.647
Leave me here. I have a score to settle.

11:37.571 --> 11:39.824
[gasping]

11:47.081 --> 11:49.708
Where'd they go, where'd they go?

11:50.501 --> 11:51.377
[Sonic gasps]

11:55.339 --> 11:56.465
Somebody hit the lights!

12:05.099 --> 12:07.476
What is that?

12:07.560 --> 12:13.232
[music swells]

12:13.315 --> 12:15.901
[Sonic] Green Hill...

12:22.700 --> 12:25.703
[laughing] The suckers fell for it!

12:25.786 --> 12:29.039
Time to hit the rendezvous point
and get the heck out of here.

12:29.123 --> 12:33.085
All right, let's see. When in doubt,
turn it off and turn it back on again.

12:33.169 --> 12:36.755
-[scoffs] How profound. Here we go.
-[beeps]

12:37.756 --> 12:40.801
[Yolkomotive powers off]

12:40.885 --> 12:45.097
[grunts] What? Where'd the power go?

12:45.181 --> 12:47.349
[clicks button]

12:47.433 --> 12:49.935
[Yolkomotive powers back on]

12:50.019 --> 12:51.479
[yells] There's the power!

12:51.562 --> 12:53.272
[Dr. Deep] Whoooaaa!

12:53.355 --> 12:55.274
What the heck is going on up there?

12:57.067 --> 13:00.070
The Chaos Council craft is behind us.

13:00.154 --> 13:02.072
Me beauty calls ta me.

13:06.327 --> 13:09.371
-Underwater? Why are we underwater?
-[yells]

13:09.455 --> 13:12.291
Well, I had to shake them loose somehow!

13:12.374 --> 13:14.710
[grunts] What is that?

13:17.087 --> 13:19.256
Eat plasma, deserters!

13:21.050 --> 13:22.760
[both yell]

13:26.972 --> 13:30.100
Mothership. Come in, Mothership!
Pick up at the rendezvous point!

13:36.565 --> 13:39.443
You'll soon be in me grasp again,
me beauty.

13:40.402 --> 13:42.112
Launch the torpedoes!

13:43.447 --> 13:46.033
[torpedoes firing]

13:46.116 --> 13:47.618
Pull up!

13:47.701 --> 13:48.994
[torpedoes drifting]

13:49.078 --> 13:50.162
[gasps]

13:50.246 --> 13:51.497
[torpedoes drifting]

13:53.332 --> 13:54.375
[sighs in relief]

13:54.458 --> 13:58.379
You won't be getting away that easy,
scoundrels. [laughs]

13:58.462 --> 13:59.421
[gasps]

14:01.006 --> 14:03.551
[yells] Dread!

14:12.935 --> 14:14.770
To the rendezvous point!

14:17.731 --> 14:18.649
[both yelp]

14:18.732 --> 14:19.608
Yes!

14:24.154 --> 14:25.322
[both yelp]

14:37.835 --> 14:40.004
You're gonna turn, right, Dread?

14:40.754 --> 14:41.714
Right?

14:43.424 --> 14:44.800
Oh, no!

14:47.094 --> 14:49.597
[all screaming]

15:01.358 --> 15:05.571
[coughing and gasping]

15:05.654 --> 15:07.907
Crazy pirate nearly killed us!

15:07.990 --> 15:09.408
[both grumble]

15:10.993 --> 15:12.703
Huh? What's that?

15:13.954 --> 15:16.498
Arrrh! It's Sonic!

15:18.375 --> 15:20.419
The Shard! Secure the Shard!

15:20.502 --> 15:22.630
[clanking]

15:23.756 --> 15:25.758
-[door dings]
-Hey!

15:25.841 --> 15:28.093
-Got it!
-[Eggforcer mumbling]

15:28.177 --> 15:29.762
[door dings]

15:30.721 --> 15:31.680
[Sonic laughs]

15:31.764 --> 15:34.141
-[Dr. Deep] Stop him!
-[Sonic] Whoo!

15:34.224 --> 15:37.519
[laughs] Run, rabbit, run!

15:39.563 --> 15:41.398
[Sonic grunts] A little help here!

15:45.277 --> 15:46.862
[grunts]

15:46.946 --> 15:48.656
Ha ha! Nice shot, Rusty!

15:49.949 --> 15:51.241
My pleasure.

15:51.325 --> 15:52.242
[plasma shooting]

15:52.326 --> 15:54.411
-Oh, my back! Argh!
-[back cracks]

15:54.495 --> 15:55.829
[grumbles in pain]

15:55.913 --> 15:57.873
More Eggforcers!

16:05.089 --> 16:06.340
[metal clinks]

16:07.800 --> 16:10.260
It's up to us now, me crew!

16:10.344 --> 16:13.555
Pirate like you've never pirated before!

16:13.639 --> 16:15.015
[grunts]

16:17.184 --> 16:18.352
[sword clangs]

16:19.061 --> 16:19.979
[Knuckles grunts]

16:20.062 --> 16:22.940
[metal clinking]

16:23.023 --> 16:23.941
[Amy grunts]

16:24.024 --> 16:25.526
-[frog ribbits]
-[crashes]

16:27.319 --> 16:29.071
[Sonic grunts]

16:29.154 --> 16:31.156
[gasps for air]

16:31.240 --> 16:32.616
Uh... oh.

16:32.700 --> 16:35.661
Thanks, rodent. Gotta fly!

16:35.744 --> 16:37.204
Not a chance!

16:37.287 --> 16:39.206
[Dr. Deep chuckles, grunts]

16:42.334 --> 16:43.961
Me beauty!

16:45.129 --> 16:46.338
[Dr. Deep] Not for long!

16:46.422 --> 16:47.548
[both grunt]

16:55.097 --> 16:57.641
[metal clinking]

16:57.725 --> 17:00.477
He scores a ten from the judges!

17:00.561 --> 17:02.646
[Eggforcers falling]

17:02.730 --> 17:07.276
[both grunting]

17:07.359 --> 17:10.279
[Knuckles screaming in slow motion] No!

17:10.362 --> 17:11.530
[laughing]

17:11.613 --> 17:13.657
So long, Captain Looser!

17:13.741 --> 17:17.077
Come back here,
you yellow-bellied barnacle!

17:19.455 --> 17:23.375
Get that shard back here,
you flying beatnik!

17:23.459 --> 17:26.920
Sonic! I got it covered here.
Go after the Shard!

17:28.338 --> 17:30.841
That's right, fetch me precious

17:30.924 --> 17:34.053
while I turn me crew on ya
to steal it back!

17:34.178 --> 17:35.012
[Knuckles grunts]

17:42.644 --> 17:43.645
Sonic!

17:43.729 --> 17:47.316
He's turned on us, Batten!
We're on our own!

17:53.739 --> 17:59.328
And so, we bid farewell
to this soggy hellscape, never to return.

17:59.411 --> 18:01.538
[Sonic spinning]

18:01.622 --> 18:03.332
-[grunts]
-[grunts in surprise]

18:04.583 --> 18:08.045
Hee hee, burn that blue hamster!

18:08.128 --> 18:10.047
[Sonic grunting]

18:10.130 --> 18:12.800
[Tails yells, grunts]

18:14.551 --> 18:16.178
Nineteen, twenty!

18:16.303 --> 18:17.179
[grunts]

18:17.262 --> 18:19.515
Twenty-one, twenty-two! [grunts]

18:21.517 --> 18:24.311
Twenty-three, twenty-four,

18:24.394 --> 18:27.856
twenty-five, twenty-six, twenty-seven!

18:27.940 --> 18:32.027
Get back, ye rust buckets.
I'll break your sea legs!

18:32.111 --> 18:33.987
He abandoned us, Capt'n?

18:34.071 --> 18:39.034
Sorry, Batten. We never
should have trusted that blue land-lover.

18:39.118 --> 18:40.202
Me Roses!

18:40.285 --> 18:42.204
[both] Aye, Capt'n!

18:42.287 --> 18:46.792
Sonic has abandoned us.
This be our final stand!

18:46.875 --> 18:48.627
-[both gasp]
-[in unison] Aye, Capt'n!

18:48.710 --> 18:50.838
-Thirty-six.
-Thirty-seven.

18:50.921 --> 18:52.005
Thirty-eight.

18:52.089 --> 18:54.424
-[Rusty] Thirty-nine...
-[Black] Forty!

18:56.426 --> 18:58.345
[spinning]

18:58.428 --> 19:00.222
-[metal clanking]
-[Dr. Deep grunts]

19:03.142 --> 19:05.769
-[Black] Fifty-four!
-[Rusty] Fifty-five.

19:05.853 --> 19:07.938
-[Black] Fifty-six!
-[Rusty] Fifty-seven.

19:08.021 --> 19:10.899
-[Black] Fifty-eight!
-[Rusty] Fifty-nine.

19:10.983 --> 19:12.693
[both] Sixty!

19:13.944 --> 19:15.320
High five!

19:15.404 --> 19:17.072
High... five?

19:23.370 --> 19:25.372
-[Dr. Deep grunting]
-[metal clinking]

19:30.043 --> 19:31.086
[Sonic yelling]

19:31.170 --> 19:32.379
[screams]

19:32.462 --> 19:33.839
[Sonic grunts]

19:33.922 --> 19:34.882
Ha ha!

19:34.965 --> 19:36.008
[grunts]

19:36.925 --> 19:37.968
[groans]

19:42.472 --> 19:44.725
Ah! [grunts]

19:44.808 --> 19:46.268
-Huh?
-Yoink!

19:46.351 --> 19:47.769
-[Sonic grunts]
-[grunts]

19:49.521 --> 19:51.648
Eat plasma, hedgehog!

19:51.732 --> 19:53.692
Aww! You got it right for once!

19:55.027 --> 19:56.987
[gasps] Oopsie pickle!

20:00.824 --> 20:03.452
And that's the way it's done.

20:06.872 --> 20:08.498
He hung us out to dry.

20:08.999 --> 20:10.709
He's a traitor, me crew.

20:10.792 --> 20:13.587
Can't be trusted, just like them!

20:13.670 --> 20:15.756
But, Dread, we had a plan.

20:15.839 --> 20:17.549
[Knuckles The Dread] Hand it over.

20:17.633 --> 20:20.344
You abandoned us, Sonic!

20:20.427 --> 20:23.430
Ye left us at the mercy o' them robuts.

20:23.513 --> 20:26.975
I'll blast 'im right b'tween the eyes.

20:27.059 --> 20:29.186
Just do not hit the Shard.

20:29.269 --> 20:32.314
I... wha... ho-- how could-- it...

20:32.397 --> 20:34.274
Last chance, Blue.

20:34.358 --> 20:37.778
The Shard or yer life!

20:37.861 --> 20:40.739
[dramatic music swells]

20:40.822 --> 20:42.157
[music ends]

20:42.241 --> 20:44.701
[closing theme plays]
